Reality TV star-cum-singer, Tope Adenibuyan, akaTeddy A, has addressed prospective BBNaija participants via a TikTok video. Teddy A in the video highlighted individuals who have no business taking part on the most watched reality TV show in Africa. Big Brother Naija announced its return for its seventh season in July with a double launch show on July 23 and July 24, 2022.   BREAKING: Panic as fire guts tank farm in Delta     Buhari arrives Daura for Sallah celebration     Sekinat’s Idamu Adugbo makes waves   This season’s winner will take home a grand prize worth N100 million including N50 million cash and other exciting prizes. With the countdown to the launch of its seventh edition, the former BBNaija “Double Wahala” housemate in his message written in Pidgin advised individuals who can’t handle trolls and controversy to stay away from participating on the reality show. Teddy A wrote: “You wan go bigbrother but you no sabi handle criticism and serious trolling. Small controversy you say depression wan kill you. “My dia sit down jejely. Fame never hungry you. Only the strong survive!”